  "text": "Advances in medical care have occurred as a result of pioneers who have continued to forge new paths in managing patients with advanced disease. Wong et al. [CITATION_1] present a unique study that examined one of the largest institutional series of patients undergoing ILIs for melanoma and compared patients who underwent excision of residual melanoma after an ILI with patients who experienced complete response. The group reported equivalent median overall survival, suggesting that regional therapy, even as a neoadjuvant/conversion strategy, might be beneficial for patients with locally aggressive disease.",
